==English==

===Etymology===
From the french word ''[[positivisme]]'', derived from ''[[positif]]'' ([[positive]]).

===Noun===
'''positivism'''

# Philosophical movement of the second half of the XIX century, that refuse every form of [[metaphysics]] and put scientific data as the only foundation of knowledge. "'''[[Logic]] positivism"''', '''"[[neopositivism]]"'''.
# [[practical|Practical]] spirit, sense of reality, [[concreteness]].

